Charge Delegates to Vote Wisely At The Party Presidential Primaries JOS – Vice President Yemi Osinbajo on Tuesday received Red Carpet reception from his supporters and delegates across 17 LGAs in Plateau state during his campaign visit to Jos, the capital of Plateau state. Osinbajo who was overwhelmed with crowd of and well wishers who were at the General Yakubu Gowon Heipang Airport, charged All Progressives Congress national delegates to the Party’s presidential convention this weekend to be patriotic and cast their votes to uphold the unity and prosperity of the country. -Advertisement- Osinbajo said he is in the presidential race because he has what it takes to continue from where his principal President Buhari will stop next year after completing his two terms in Office to consolidate on security, job creation, and agricultural production and industrial revolution towards a shock absorbent economy. Osinbajo was received at the Government House by a mammoth crowd of party faithful and surging Christian groups chanting hymns and dancing, VP Osibanjo is the Man. Osinbajo had earlier paid a courtesy call on the Jos Monarch, the Gbong Gwom Jos, His Royal Highness, Jacob Gyang Buba where he also spoke on national emergencies and imperatives as industrial climate, infrastructure, and energy security. Harping on skills and human capital development, Osinbajo noted that “investing in people is worthwhile”, promising that if elected as the president of Nigeria, his government “will increase opportunities for young people to acquire work experience to increase their chances of finding long term work”. He also promised to “provide sustainable financing options to digital and creative sector skills and talent providers across the country”, as well as “establish one digital and creativity sector skills centre of excellence in each state of the country”. POLL Osinbajo, who was received at the Yakubu Gowon Airport, Heipang, by the state Deputy Governor, Sonni Gwanle Tyoden and the State APC Chairman, Rufus Bature, and other Party officials, also paid a courtesy visit on Governor Simon Lalong at his Government House residence.